              <Math tex="|\\psi\\rangle" /> forward to downstream protocols.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>

          <p>
            <strong>(c) Heralded — two-node, memory carrier.</strong> Two distant memories
            each emit a photon that travels to a midpoint Bell-state measurement; a click
            pattern there projects the two memories into a Bell state. Every photon is
            consumed at the midpoint — the surviving state lives in the memories at the
            two endpoints, not in any photonic mode. This is the heralded entanglement
            generation in Azuma's worked example (RMP 95.045006
            §II.B) <SourceNote id="azuma-rmp-95" /> and the primitive that every
            memory-based repeater is built on.
          </p>

